-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Virgin America, Rowan Companies, Walgreen
-- 
-- Wed Dec 24, 2014 01:25AM EST
-- None



Dec 24 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S. companies, including Virgin America and Walgreen, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Virgin America <VA.O>: Barclays starts with overweight rating; price target of $42 * Rowan Companies <RDC.N>: Susquehanna cuts price target to $21 from $24; rating neutral * Walgreen <WAG.N>: Barclays raises price target to $72 from $68; rating equal weight  Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Continental Resources <CLR.N>: Barclays cuts target to $42 from $44; rating overweight  * FirstEnergy <FE.N>: Jefferies raises price target to $47 from $45; rating buy * Rowan Companies <RDC.N>: Susquehanna cuts price target to $21 from $24; rating neutral * Virgin America <VA.O>: Barclays starts with overweight rating; price target of $42 * Walgreen <WAG.N>: Barclays raises price target to $72 from $68; rating equal weight